cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and watershed-based postprocessing strategies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of CNNs also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the application of the proposed method to 3D confocal microscopy images could also make cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
